{
  "texts": [
    "In this study, we propose a new hybrid system based on deep learning models that accurately detect electricity theft in smart grids while also being efficient.",
    "The first step involves preprocessing the data and replacing the missing values using a simple imputer method.",
    "Next, we use the standard-scalar approach to execute a min-max operation for data normalization.",
    "After data preparation is finished, we obtain samples for typical users.",
    "We then balance the data using k-means SMOTE to create samples for fraudulent users by altering honest samples with current theft attacks."
  ]
}